[
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Since  $j$  is an affine morphism, there are no higher direct images and we obtain followings :",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n$$\n\\mathrm{ch}E_{\\mathcal{L}} = \\pi_{2*}(\\mathrm{ch}(j_{*}\\mathcal{O}_{Z_{2}})\\pi_{1}^{*}\\mathrm{ch}\\mathcal{L}\\pi_{1}^{*}\\mathrm{td}T_{X})\n$$\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "and",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n$$\n\\mathrm{ch}j_{*}\\mathcal{O}_{Z_{2}} = j_{*}((\\mathrm{td}\\mathcal{N})^{-1})\n$$\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "by applying the Grothendieck- Riemann- Roch theorem. Note that  $\\pi_2\\circ j = \\rho$",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "By the projection formula, we have:",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n$$\n\\begin{array}{rl} & {\\mathrm{ch}E_{\\mathcal{L}} = \\pi_{2*}(\\mathrm{ch}(j_{*}\\mathcal{O}_{Z_{2}})\\pi_{1}^{*}\\mathrm{ch}\\mathcal{L}\\pi_{1}^{*}\\mathrm{td}T_{X})}\\\\ & {\\qquad = \\pi_{2*}(j_{*}\\mathrm{ch}(\\mathrm{td}\\mathcal{N})^{-1}\\pi_{1}^{*}\\mathrm{ch}\\mathcal{L}\\pi_{1}^{*}\\mathrm{td}T_{X})}\\\\ & {\\qquad = (\\pi_{2*}\\circ j_{*})(\\mathrm{ch}(\\mathrm{td}\\mathcal{N})^{-1}j^{*}\\pi_{1}^{*}\\mathrm{ch}\\mathcal{L}j^{*}\\pi_{1}^{*}\\mathrm{td}T_{X})}\\\\ & {\\qquad = \\rho_{*}((\\mathrm{td}\\mathcal{N})^{-1}q^{*}\\mathrm{ch}\\mathcal{L}q^{*}\\mathrm{td}T_{X}).} \\end{array}\n$$\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Consider the sheaf sequence",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n$$\n0\\to \\mathcal{N}^*\\to q^*\\Omega_X\\to \\mathcal{O}_E(-E)\\to 0\n$$\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "as given in [6] Lemma 2.1]. (Note that the morphism  $q$  in proposition 3.1 and in [6] are different morphisms.) Taking dual of this sequence, we obtain :",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n$$\n0\\to q^{*}T_{X}\\to \\mathcal{N}\\to \\mathcal{E}xt^{1}(\\mathcal{O}_{E}(-E),\\mathcal{O}_{Z_{2}})\\to 0.\n$$\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Therefore we have",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n$$\n(\\mathrm{td}\\mathcal{N})^{-1} = (q^{*}\\mathrm{td}T_{X})^{-1}\\cdot (\\mathrm{td}\\mathcal{E}xt^{1}(\\mathcal{O}_{E}(-E),\\mathcal{O}_{Z_{2}}))^{-1}.\n$$\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "To evaluate  $\\mathrm{td}\\mathcal{E}xt^{1}(\\mathcal{O}_{E}(- E),\\mathcal{O}_{Z_{2}})$  , we consider the exact sequence :",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n$$\n0\\to \\mathcal{O}_{Z_2}(-2E)\\to \\mathcal{O}_{Z_2}(-E)\\to \\mathcal{O}_E(-E)\\to 0.\n$$\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Taking the dual of this sequence, we have :",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n$$\n0\\to \\mathcal{O}_{Z_2}(E)\\to \\mathcal{O}_{Z_2}(2E)\\to \\mathcal{E}xt^1 (\\mathcal{O}_E(-E),\\mathcal{O}_{Z_2})\\to 0.\n$$\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Therefore, we obtain",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n$$\n\\mathrm{td}\\mathcal{E}xt^{1}(\\mathcal{O}_{E}(-E),\\mathcal{O}_{Z_{2}}) = \\frac{2E}{1 - e^{-2E}} /\\frac{E}{1 - e^{-E}} = \\frac{2}{1 + e^{-E}}\n$$\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "and",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "equation",
        "text": "\n$$\n\\begin{array}{rl} & {\\mathrm{ch}E_{\\mathcal{L}} = \\rho_{*}\\left(q^{*}\\mathrm{ch}\\mathcal{L}\\frac{1 + e^{-E}}{2}\\right)}\\\\ & {\\qquad = \\rho_{*}\\left(\\left(1 + \\eta^{*}h_{1} + \\frac{1}{2!}\\eta^{*}h_{1}^{2} + \\frac{1}{3!}\\eta^{*}h_{1}^{3} + \\dots\\right)\\cdot \\left(1 - \\frac{1}{2} E + \\frac{1}{4} E^{2} - \\frac{1}{12} E^{3} + \\dots\\right)\\right)}\\\\ & {\\qquad = \\rho_{*}\\left(1 + \\left(\\eta^{*}h_{1} - \\frac{1}{2} E\\right) + \\left(\\frac{1}{2}\\eta^{*}h_{1}^{2} - \\frac{1}{2}\\eta^{*}h_{1}\\cdot E + \\frac{1}{4} E^{2}\\right) + \\dots\\right)}\\\\ & {\\qquad = 2 + (H - \\delta) + \\left(\\frac{1}{2}\\rho_{*}\\eta^{*}h_{1}^{2} - \\frac{1}{2}\\rho_{*}(\\eta^{*}h_{1}\\cdot E) + \\frac{1}{4}\\rho_{*}E^{2}\\right) + \\dots .} \\end{array}\n$$\n",
        "text_format": "latex",
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "So we obtain  $c_{1}(E_{\\mathcal{L}}) = H - \\delta$",
        "page_idx": 0
    }
]